y spans the fields of computerized tomography ultrasound imaging nuclear medicine magnetic resonance imaging mri and digital mammography adaptive filtering projects have often been done in conjunction with research groups in the school of medicine projects involving pattern recognition hypothesis testing classification cluster analysis and statistical inference have created connections with the statistics department research on probability theory and random processes has been conducted with the mathematics department next retrieved from http ee stanford edu gradhandbook information_systems_laboratory_ 28isl 29 categories research labs handbook page discussion view source history what links here related changes upload file special pages permanent link this page was last modified 20 58 21 august 2008 this page has been accessed 4585 times privacy policy about stanford electrical engineering department graduate handbook disclaimers original design by paul gu modified for ee by eric wheeler
